experience.description:
*Conducted extensive diagnostic consultations on patients and gave therapeutic recommendations. 
*Provided Individual, multi-modality therapy to children and adolescents.
*Prescribed psychopharmacology geared for children and childhood mental and neurological issues.
*Consulted on children in the pediatric inpatient unit and assessed their mental/emotional state.
*Treated children and adolescents residing in the state inpatient child psychiatry hospital. 

Fellowship to Attend The American Association of General Psychiatry conference in Toronto, BC;
Poster Presentation on Bulimia Nervosa and the Link with Obsessive-Compulsive Traits at AAP;
Film-Forum Presenter and Discussion Facilitator on Antisocial Disorder in Girls at AAP;
Award to Attend The American Association of Child and Adolescent Psychiatry in San Diego, CA; 
Award of "Women in Psychiatry" at AACAP.

Represented numerous public and private companies in various industries (including health care, telecommunications, internet, and other high-technology industries) in the areas of: 
• Venture capital, private equity, debt financings and recapitalizations (including numerous venture investments in Chinese companies); 
•  Mergers and acquisition transactions;
•  Company formation and start-up issues;
• Securities regulatory compliance (including initial public offering, cross-border 144A offering and periodic SEC filings

As a consulting attorney for USAID-funded Macedonia Financial Sector Strengthening Project, led and participated in numerous legislative efforts to promote capital market reform in former Yugoslav republic:
• Drafted proposed amended securities law (and annotations for public comment) to conform to international standards and EU Directives which was submitted to Parliament;
• Drafted and revised implementing regulations pertaining to national pension reform which were successfully enacted into law;  
•  Collaborated on a daily basis with senior government officials and other NGO project leaders.

As in-house counsel for an institutional investor with over $35 billion in assets under management (including third-party funds), substantial exposure to all aspects of private placement investing (including restructurings and workouts):
•  Structured, negotiated and documented over 45 private placement investments in excess of $1 billion, including investment grade and below investment grade debt, mezzanine, equity and other structured investments in wide range of industries and countries;  
•  Successfully restructured 8 defaulted investments, including intercreditor and security terms;
•  Negotiated over 20 technology transfer agreements on behalf of the Law Department;
•  Interacted daily with senior executives to provide wide range of legal counsel in a business context and regularly supervised outside counsel.

Negotiated and drafted transaction documents for complex financing transactions (domestic and international), including project financings, on behalf of multilateral agencies, commercial lenders, public governmental entities and companies:
•  Lead associate on major Mexican telecommunications financing and restructuring of Indonesian power plant financing;
•  Participated in two stadium financing transactions; 
•  Advised lenders on debt restructuring in major Mexican steel company (AHMSA) insolvency;
•  Established tax-preferential foreign investment fund on behalf of Mexican clients;
•  Advised ratings agencies in connection with international project financings and securitizations; 
•  Drafted and negotiated wide variety of contracts for clients related to asset sales/purchases, construction agreements, mergers and ongoing business operations.
